            "answer_text": "\u201cWhen, where and why did Winston Churchill say, \u201cNever let a good crisis go to waste? \u201d\u201d There is some speculation that Churchill said that in a meeting with Stalin & Roosevelt that first brought up the formation of the United Nations. But there is no actual confirmation of that other than \u201cit sounds like something he [Churchill] would say\u201d - not even viable hearsay. A similar quote was used by Rahm Emanuel and the thought was in Saul Alinsky\u2019s \u201cRules for Radicals\u201d, but I have not been able to find any direct attribution of that statement to Churchill, and since so many things he said has been recorded and archived, it is unlikely that such a statement would have been missed, had he said it. ",
