                "href": "/profile/Dennis-Weber-14"
            },
            "answer_text": "I don't know of any proof that he did say this. I know there are stories that he may have said it at Yalta, but 1) there is no proof, and 2) it doesn't add up; many historians think FDR gave away the farm to Stalin at Yalta and Churchill wasn't able to stop him. So if he saw Yalta as an opportunity, he certainly didn't cash in. I know Rahm Emmanuel, the former mayor of Chicago as well as President Obama's former chief of staff has said this. I know dictators like Hitler and Stalin have lived by this motto\u2014- but I can't find anywhere proving Churchill actually said it. That being said, there are plenty of good Churchill quotes out there. One of my favorites is \"if you are going through hell, keep going\". ",
